Project Overview

OpenTrack is a command-line project management tool built in Python. It demonstrates data structures, user input, file handling, and basic data analysis.

---

Main Variables and Their Purpose

- `project` (Tuple) → Stores project information (name, version, year, language, lead). Used because tuples are immutable.
- `contributors` (List of Dictionaries) → Stores details of all contributors (name, role, language, commits, country, status).
- `issues` (List of Dictionaries) → Holds all created issues with id, title, type, priority, reporter and status.
- `names` and `sorted_names` (List) → Used to extract and sort contributor names.
- `reporters` (Set) → Stores unique reporter names.
- `tech_stack` (Set) → Stores programming languages used by contributors.
- `priorities_set` (Set) → Checks whether Critical priority exists.
- `priority_count` (Dictionary) → Counts number of issues for each priority level.
- `status_groups` (Dictionary) → Groups issue titles according to their status.
- `reporter_count` (Dictionary) → Counts issues per reporter to find the top reporter.
- `urgent` (List) → Contains titles of all Critical and High priority issues.
- `folder_name` (String) → Name of the folder created to save reports.
- `report_path` & `csv_path` (String) → Full file paths for project_report.txt and issues.csv.

